{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_43","type":"agent_message","text":"`JdkAugmenter` is the root problem: Selenium 3.141.59 builds the proxy interface list with a raw `HashSet` and then calls `Proxy.newProxyInstance` on `set.toArray(...)`. That means the proxy order is JVM-instance dependent, which is why each rerun keeps surfacing a different missing proxy signature. I’m checking whether the repo already has a supported way to register these proxies programmatically during image build; if not, I’ll call out that metadata-only fixes here are inherently unstable."}}
